This paper deals with the use of gaze behaviour to predict the rating of text quality, which involves estimating subjective aspects of the text. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computer Vision (cs.CV). However, since the paper focuses on the use of cognitive information (gaze behaviour) to predict text quality, we can assume that it is more likely to belong to the first two categories, i.e., cs.HC and cs.CL. The other categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more focused on technical aspects of machine learning and computer vision.
